---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { features } from '../config/features';
---

<Layout>
	<main class="site-shell">
		<section class="hero" aria-label="Baker James Farm Homestead Concept">
			<nav class="nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
				<a class="brand" href="/">
					<img src="/logo-mark.svg" alt="" width="40" height="40" />
					<span>Baker James Farm</span>
				</a>
				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="#vision">Vision</a>
					<a href="#homesteads">Homesteads</a>
					<a href="#land">Land</a>
					<a href="#visit">Experience</a>
					<a href="/location-research/">Location</a>
					{features.draftPages && <a href="/investor-packet/">Investor Packet</a>}
				</div>
			</nav>

			<div class="hero-content">
				<p class="eyebrow">Noblesville, Indiana | Ultra-premium homestead concept</p>
				<h1>Private estate homes rooted in gardens, prairie, and farm-venue culture.</h1>
				<p class="intro">
					Baker James Farm is a proposed hybrid agritourism development in Noblesville:
					five private multi-acre homesteads shaped by architectural discipline, cultivated
					gardens, native prairie restoration, walking paths, and a farm-venue experience.
				</p>
				<div class="actions">
					<a class="button primary" href="#homesteads">Explore the plan</a>
					<a class="button secondary" href="/location-research/">Why this location</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section intro-section" id="vision">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Development vision</p>
				<h2>Rural luxury with a cultivated farm rhythm.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="narrative">
				<p>
					The concept preserves the feeling of a working Hamilton County landscape while
					adding a carefully scaled ultra-premium residential layer. Homes are intentionally
					few, land is intentionally generous, and the shared open space becomes the primary
					amenity.
				</p>
				<p>
					The design language leans estate-like rather than suburban: warm wood,
					hand-laid stone, simple rooflines, garden courts, greenhouse moments, gravel
					walks, orchard edges, and views across restored prairie.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section" id="homesteads">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Five homesteads</p>
				<h2>Private acreage, shared identity.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="homestead-grid">
				<article>
					<span>01</span>
					<h3>Multi-acre homesites</h3>
					<p>Each homesite has room for gardens, small barns, outdoor kitchens, and quiet views.</p>
				</article>
				<article>
					<span>02</span>
					<h3>European material palette</h3>
					<p>Timber beams, natural stone, limewashed textures, metal roofs, and restrained detailing.</p>
				</article>
				<article>
					<span>03</span>
					<h3>Estate-scale site planning</h3>
					<p>Homes are placed with privacy, long views, and generous open land between them.</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="image-band" aria-label="European stone and timber farm buildings">
			<div class="image-copy">
				<p class="label">Architectural character</p>
				<h2>Framed by stone, timber, orchard rows, and working garden rooms.</h2>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="market" id="land">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Land strategy</p>
				<h2>Homes, venue land, restoration, and trails each have a clear role.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="land-list">
				<p>The farm and venue lot is kept distinct from the residential homesites so guest activity has its own center of gravity.</p>
				<p>Multi-acre home lots are arranged for privacy, long views, gardens, and a quiet residential edge.</p>
				<p>Restoration areas focus on invasive cleanup, native habitat, pollinator support, and a continuous wildlife movement corridor.</p>
				<p>A soft-surface walking path network connects homesteads, overlooks, farm edges, and restoration areas without feeling overbuilt.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section plan-section" aria-label="Conceptual site plan">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Conceptual site plan</p>
				<h2>A landscape-first plan with distinct public, private, and ecological zones.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="plan-grid">
				<article class="plan-card">
					<span>Farm / venue lot</span>
					<h3>Public-facing farm culture</h3>
					<p>Seasonal gatherings, workshops, farm stand moments, and garden programming stay concentrated on the dedicated venue land.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="plan-card">
					<span>Home lots</span>
					<h3>Private multi-acre living</h3>
					<p>Homesites remain quiet and residential, with room for private gardens, outbuildings, outdoor kitchens, and generous buffers.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="plan-card">
					<span>Restoration area</span>
					<h3>Native wildlife corridor</h3>
					<p>Green space becomes active habitat: remove invasives, restore native plantings, and create a protected passage for wildlife.</p>
				</article>
				<article class="plan-card">
					<span>Walking paths</span>
					<h3>Soft circulation</h3>
					<p>Walking paths stitch the land together for residents and guided experiences while keeping vehicles and visitors controlled.</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section location-summary" id="location">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Why Noblesville</p>
				<h2>Open-space living just outside downtown Noblesville.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="narrative">
				<p>
					The concept belongs in Noblesville's civic-recreation fabric: close to parks,
					trails, golf, youth sports, downtown small businesses, and the city's growing
					open-space network.
				</p>
				<p>
					That context makes the project feel less like a subdivision and more like a
					landscape-led extension of Noblesville's parks, trails, gardens, and downtown
					visitor economy.
				</p>
				<a class="market-link" href="/location-research/">Read the location research</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section visit" id="visit">
			<div>
				<p class="label">Agritourism layer</p>
				<h2>An adjacent farm venue for seasonal visits, workshops, and slow weekends.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="experience-grid">
				<p>Small farm stand days, native plant walks, harvest dinners, flower cutting mornings, and craft workshops can bring visitors to the adjacent farm-venue land without overwhelming the residential scale.</p>
				<p>The public experience is focused near the entry and farm buildings, while the five homesteads remain quiet, private, and visually buffered by restoration areas, gardens, and orchard plantings.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	:global(html) {
		scroll-behavior: smooth;
		background: #f7f3eb;
		color: #1e241d;
		font-family:
			Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
	}

	:global(body) {
		min-height: 100%;
	}

	.site-shell {
		min-height: 100vh;
		background: #f7f3eb;
	}

	.hero {
		position: relative;
		min-height: 88vh;
		display: grid;
		align-content: space-between;
		padding: 24px clamp(18px, 4vw, 56px) 72px;
		overflow: hidden;
		background:
			linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(15, 17, 12, 0.92), rgba(15, 17, 12, 0.58)),
			url("/images/baker-james-farm-luxury-homestead.png") center / cover;
		color: #fffdf6;
	}

	.hero::after {
		content: "";
		position: absolute;
		inset: auto 0 0;
		height: 30%;
		background: linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.34), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0));
		pointer-events: none;
	}

	.nav,
	.hero-content {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
	}

	.nav {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 24px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 253, 246, 0.24);
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: rgba(15, 17, 12, 0.72);
	}

	a {
		color: inherit;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.brand {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.55rem);
		font-weight: 800;
	}

	.brand img {
		width: 40px;
		height: 40px;
		border-radius: 8px;
	}

	.nav-links {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: clamp(14px, 3vw, 32px);
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.hero-content {
		max-width: 900px;
		padding-top: 22vh;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.label {
		margin: 0 0 14px;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3,
	p {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	h1 {
		max-width: 880px;
		margin-bottom: 18px;
		font-size: clamp(2.9rem, 6.3vw, 6.6rem);
		line-height: 0.94;
	}

	h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 4rem);
		line-height: 1;
	}

	h3 {
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		font-size: 1.35rem;
	}

	.intro {
		max-width: 640px;
		font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: #f4ead7;
	}

	.actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-top: 30px;
	}

	.button,
	.market-link {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		min-height: 46px;
		padding: 0 18px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		font-weight: 800;
	}

	.primary {
		background: #f7c948;
		color: #202316;
	}

	.secondary {
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
		color: #fffdf6;
	}

	.market-link {
		width: fit-content;
		border: 1px solid #a65f34;
		color: #7c3f22;
	}

	.section,
	.market {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.95fr) minmax(280px, 1.05fr);
		gap: clamp(28px, 5vw, 72px);
		padding: clamp(56px, 9vw, 112px) clamp(18px, 4vw, 56px);
	}

	.section {
		background: #f7f3eb;
	}

	.label {
		color: #7c3f22;
	}

	.narrative {
		display: grid;
		gap: 18px;
		color: #53594e;
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.homestead-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 16px;
	}

	.plan-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 16px;
	}

	article {
		min-height: 230px;
		padding: 22px;
		border: 1px solid #ded4c3;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fffaf0;
	}

	article span {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 42px;
		color: #a65f34;
		font-weight: 900;
	}

	article p,
	.plan-card p,
	.visit p,
	.land-list p {
		color: #5e6357;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.plan-card {
		min-height: 240px;
	}

	.plan-card span {
		margin-bottom: 36px;
	}

	.image-band {
		min-height: 58vh;
		display: grid;
		align-items: end;
		padding: clamp(56px, 9vw, 112px) clamp(18px, 4vw, 56px);
		background:
			linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(12, 15, 10, 0.88), rgba(12, 15, 10, 0.52)),
			url("/images/baker-james-farm-venue-gardens.png") center / cover;
		color: #fffdf6;
	}

	.image-copy {
		max-width: 800px;
	}

	.image-copy .label {
		color: #f7c948;
	}

	.market {
		align-items: end;
		background: #24311f;
		color: #fffdf6;
	}

	.market .label {
		color: #f7c948;
	}

	.market .land-list p {
		color: #f7f0df;
	}

	.land-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	.visit {
		align-items: start;
	}

	.experience-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	.visit p {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 820px) {
		.nav {
			align-items: flex-start;
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		.hero {
			min-height: 92vh;
			padding-bottom: 52px;
		}

		.hero-content {
			padding-top: 18vh;
		}

		.section,
		.market {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.homestead-grid,
		.plan-grid,
		.experience-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
